RACE.RACE_TEXT: Ed Burke Million Futurity Trial LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 350 Y Dirt CR: 80. Futurity Trial Purse 6000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. 126lbs. (No sex allowance). Horses which qualify for the finals must remain on the grounds until 48 hours after the finals have run. All horses must be on the grounds 15 days prior to trial entry day.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKIN WITH ENERGY away well, asked right handed passing the gap, shifted out when asked, asked again midway and lugged out approaching the wire. REMEMBER JOHN away cleanly, drifted out slightly when asked passing the gap, kept to task to the wire in a solid effort. WARRIOR SOUL away well, head and head early with winner, slightly weaved midway and outfinished for second. FLASH DASH broke in and brushed at the start, asked steadily early, kept in a drive to the wire while being outkicked. READY FOR IT broke in and brushed with rival at the start, steadily asked right handed throughout in a even effort. CAVA JOHN CASH broke in, shied out early after being asked, lost his path and lacked room rest of the way. RHEA bumped twice at the start, lost path early, lugged out early, and saved thereafter. TWICE OVER came in and bumped rival twice at the start, floated out early by inside rival, and lacked a response in behind rivals.

ENTRY.NAME: Warrior Soul
ENTRY.OWNER: Gomez Jaime H and Moya Juan Humberto

ENTRY.NAME: Rhea
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped twice start, lugged out early

ENTRY.NAME: Twice Over
ENTRY.COMMENT: came in/bumped twice start, floated out early

ENTRY.NAME: Cava John Cash
ENTRY.COMMENT: first time gelding, shied early, lacked room

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Ed Burke Million Futurity Trial LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 350 Y Dirt CR: 79. Futurity Trial Purse 6000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. 126lbs. (No sex allowance). Horses which qualify for the finals must remain on the grounds until 48 hours after the finals have run. All horses must be on the grounds 15 days prior to trial entry day.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEVINS WISE CORONA away cleanly and had a wide path, lugged in two paths early, asked right handed and lugged in another two paths, hand ridden rest of the way in a convincing win. KICKIN FAMOUS came out three paths at the start, kept trying to get in throughout, asked right handed once, kept under a cautious drive to the wire while getting up for second. MR CARTEL JESS broke in, asked right handed early, asked again midway and nosed out for second. JUST WATCH HER away cleanly while breaking in, altered out midway under urging when rival lugged in, kept to task to the wire in a solid try. THREES COMPANY broke in and bumped rival twice at the start, asked midway and kept to task to the wire. GOOD AS CANDY bumped at the start, briefly crowded early, drifted in under urging passing the gap, asked again midway and failed to respond. TWO SWEET FOR YOU off bit slow, had a wide path, had a bit awkward strides while failing to threaten. AJ PURE GOLD off slow while coming in at the start, asked right handed early and shifted out, kept under mild hand ride to the wire thereafter.

ENTRY.NAME: Kickin Famous
ENTRY.OWNER: Flores Jose Antonio Gordon Robyn and Rodriguez Ricardo
ENTRY.COMMENT: came out start, leaning in throughout, up for 2nd wire

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STANLEY CARTEL bumped on the hind at the start, drifted in two paths early, kept to a drive while edging away. ATTACKED away cleanly, slightly bobbled passing the eighth pole, kept under a drive to hold on for second. TELLER PERRY MRL broke out, kept under a drive, minor drifting in spots in a solid effort. DAWSON LEGATE away cleanly, had a wide path throughout, kept to task in a even effort. VERBOSITY bit slow and bumped rival at the start, asked right handed early, hand ridden second half of the race in a one paced effort. DELIGHTFUL AGAIN away a step slow, lost path and took up early, saved thereafter. HEART OF DYNASTY bumped by inside rival at the start, corrected and drifted out early, and lacked needed response late. CORONA JEWELS off slow and bumped outside rival at the start, angled in passing the gap, and rider saved the final third of the race.

THOUGHTS TO REMEMBER bumped at the start, steadily asked right handed early, proved no match for top two while holding third, fell past the wire and walked into the van to be vanned off.
